ROS kernel
==========

ROS is a kernel, written completely in rust.

-------------------------------------------

Progress
========
Currently, ROS is in its early stage.
The kernel development started on June 21st, 2026.

Contributing, issues, and pull requests
=======================================
Contributions are welcome.
Make sure, when contributing, to follow clean code conducts, and document everything to make it easy for others.

Issues
------
If you find a bug, or noticed something you can't solve by yourself, file an issue. We will try to review the issue and solve it, if applicable.
Make sure to add a "How to replicate" section, and list what you've tried.

Pull requests
-------------
We accept pull requests. 
When committing your changes into your PR branch, make sure to add a Signed-off-by.
Pull requests are going to be reviewed, and possibly, merged.

Development
===========
You can clone this repo with `git clone https://github.com/SauloHS/ros`.

Dependencies
------------
Rust toolchain and components
You need rustc 1.98.0-nightly 2026-06-20 to build the kernel.
You also need rust-src and llvm-tools components to build the kernel. Add them with `rustup component add rust-src llvm-tools`.

Bare-metal Target
Run `rustup target add x86_64-unknown-none` to set the target.

To run and open QEMU, run `cargo run`. To build only, without opening QEMU, run `cargo build`.


Project tree
============
src/main.rs                  # Runs QEMU
kernel/
├── src/
│   ├── main.rs              # Kernel entry point
│   ├── arch/x86_64/         # Architecture-specific (GDT, IDT, paging, init)
│   ├── mm/                  # Memory management (allocator)
│   ├── drivers/             # Hardware drivers (video, keyboard)
│   └── sched/               # Scheduling (async executor, tasks)
tools/codecheck/             # Code quality checker

Last edited by Saulo Henrique at June 26th, 2026.

